Nigeria has approved the request by the United States government for the extradition of the disgraced Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), Abba Kyari. Kyari was accused of committing wife fraud, money laundering and identity theft. SaharaReporters Media He was also accused of working with Ramon Abbas, aka Hushpuppi, who has pleaded guilty to Internet fraud. A grand jury in April 2021 filed an indictment against Kyari with the approval of the U.S. District Court for the Central District of California. On Wednesday, the Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami (SAN), filed an application before the Chief Judge of the Federal High Court in Abuja for Kyari’s extradition. The application marked: FHC/ABJ/CS/249/2022 was filed under the Extradition Act, IO Nigeria reports. 



